Year: SOURCE: Social Security Administration, Master Earnings File, 1 percent sample.
Wage and salary: a. Workers with earnings in both wage and salary employment and self-employment are counted in each type of employment but only once in the total.
Total: c. Totals do not necessarily equal the sum of rounded components.
Women: e. For all workers, medians relate to combined earnings from wage and salary employment and self-employment. For all wage and salary workers, medians relate to wages and salaries only.
